# Cursor Rules for Tutory - Pure CSS Project

## Project Context

This is a **pure CSS project** that styles a Bootstrap-based portal. We cannot modify HTML directly - only CSS can be changed.

## Core Principles

1. **Pure CSS Only**: All changes must be made through CSS. No HTML modifications are possible.
2. **Bootstrap Override Strategy**: The portal uses Bootstrap, so we target Bootstrap classes and components.
3. **"Brutal Force" Positioning**: Use aggressive CSS positioning techniques to reposition elements when needed.
4. **High Specificity**: Use high-specificity selectors and `!important` when necessary to override Bootstrap defaults.

## CSS Writing Guidelines

### Selector Strategy

- Prefer ID selectors when available: `#element-id`
- Chain Bootstrap classes for specificity: `.container .row .col-md-6`
- Use attribute selectors for flexible targeting: `[class*="bootstrap-class"]`
- Combine with pseudo-selectors: `.card:first-child`, `.btn:hover`

### Positioning Techniques

- Use `position: absolute` or `position: fixed` for precise positioning
- Leverage `transform: translate()` for fine adjustments
- Override Bootstrap's flexbox/grid with `!important` when needed
- Use `z-index` to control stacking order
- **Modern Layout**: Use flexbox/grid for modern component layouts (alignment, spacing, gaps)
- **Chained Selectors**: Target nested Bootstrap structures: `.card.custom-card .row > .col-12:first-child`

### Bootstrap Class Overrides

Common Bootstrap classes to target:

- Grid: `.container`, `.row`, `.col-*`, `.col-md-*`, `.col-lg-*`
- Components: `.card`, `.btn`, `.navbar`, `.modal`, `.dropdown`
- Utilities: `.mt-*`, `.mb-*`, `.p-*`, `.d-*`, `.text-*`
- Forms: `.form-control`, `.form-group`, `.input-group`

### Code Style

- Use `!important` when overriding Bootstrap defaults
- Add comments explaining complex positioning logic
- Group related overrides together
- Document which Bootstrap classes are being overridden

### Modern Layout Patterns (Proven Successful)

- **Card Styling**: Use larger border-radius (12px), generous padding (32px), modern shadows
- **Flexbox Alignment**: Use `display: flex`, `align-items: center`, `gap` for spacing
- **Visual Hierarchy**: Use borders, separators, and spacing to create clear sections
- **Hover Effects**: Add smooth transitions, transform effects, and background changes
- **Responsive Design**: Use media queries with mobile-first adjustments
- **Modern Buttons**: Subtle backgrounds, borders, hover animations with transform/box-shadow

## File Structure

- `advanced.css` - Main stylesheet (all CSS goes here)
- `PROJECT_APPROACH.md` - Project documentation
- `.cursorrules` - This file

## When Writing CSS

1. **Identify the target**: Determine which Bootstrap classes or elements need styling
2. **Check specificity**: Ensure your selector has enough specificity to override Bootstrap
3. **Use positioning**: Apply positioning properties (`position`, `top`, `left`, `transform`, etc.) to reposition elements
4. **Modern Layout First**: Prefer flexbox/grid for layout, use absolute positioning only when necessary
5. **Add Interactions**: Include hover effects, transitions, and visual feedback for better UX
6. **Test responsiveness**: Consider how changes affect different screen sizes with media queries
7. **Document**: Add comments explaining complex positioning logic and modern patterns used

## Example Patterns

### Modern Card Layout (Proven Pattern)

```css
/* Modern card container with enhanced styling */
.legend-week-activities.card.custom-card {
  border-radius: 12px !important;
  padding: 32px !important;
  box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5), 0 0 0 1px rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.15) !important;
  position: relative !important;
  overflow: hidden !important;
}

/* Modern header with flexbox alignment */
.legend-week-activities.card.custom-card h2 {
  display: flex !important;
  align-items: center !important;
  gap: 12px !important;
  margin-bottom: 12px !important;
}

/* Modern list items with hover effects */
.legend-week-item {
  display: flex !important;
  align-items: center !important;
  gap: 12px !important;
  padding: 12px 16px !important;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03) !important;
  border-radius: 8px !important;
  transition: all 0.3s ease !important;
}

.legend-week-item:hover {
  background: rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.05) !important;
  transform: translateX(4px) !important;
}

/* Modern buttons with hover animations */
.week-view-links a {
  display: inline-flex !important;
  align-items: center !important;
  gap: 8px !important;
  padding: 12px 24px !important;
  transition: all 0.3s ease !important;
}

.week-view-links a:hover {
  transform: translateY(-2px) !important;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.2) !important;
}
```

### Positioning Overrides

```css
/* Override Bootstrap card positioning */
.card.custom-card {
  position: relative !important;
  top: -20px !important;
  transform: translateX(10px) !important;
}

/* Override Bootstrap grid */
.container .row {
  display: flex !important;
  flex-direction: column-reverse !important;
}
```

## Important Reminders

- We cannot modify HTML - only CSS
- The portal uses Bootstrap - target Bootstrap classes
- Use aggressive positioning when needed ("brutal force" approach)
- **Prefer modern layouts**: Flexbox/grid over absolute positioning when possible
- **Enhance UX**: Add hover effects, transitions, and visual feedback
- Always test in the actual portal environment
- Keep track of overridden Bootstrap classes
- Use chained selectors for nested Bootstrap structures: `.parent .child > .grandchild`
